wiki.summary: “FE!N” reunites Playboi Carti and Travis Scott following 2018’s “Love Hurts”. It is also one of Sheck Wes‘ only released performances, having not released an album as of the release of UTOPIA other than MUDBOY. The Circus Maximus movie version features a full verse from Sheck Wes, while the commercially released version features only Sheck Wes ad-libs. wiki.content: “FE!N” reunites Playboi Carti and Travis Scott following 2018’s “Love Hurts”. It is also one of Sheck Wes‘ only released performances, having not released an album as of the release of UTOPIA other than MUDBOY. The Circus Maximus movie version features a full verse from Sheck Wes, while the commercially released version features only Sheck Wes ad-libs. The allegiance of the three rappers introduced a different soundscape from their other music. Travis Scott experiments with higher pitches of voice, whilst Playboi Carti does the opposite and adopts a deeper voice heard on many of his speculated third album, MUSIC’s snippets.
